# HIPAA Compliance & Security

## Core Principles
1. **Minimum Necessary**: Only access/display the minimum PHI needed for the task
2. **Encryption Everywhere**: AES-256 at rest, TLS 1.3 in transit
3. **Audit Everything**: Every PHI access logged with who/what/when
4. **Session Security**: Auto-timeout, secure token handling, memory cleanup

## Authentication & Sessions
- Supabase Auth with JWT tokens (short-lived: 1 hour)
- Refresh tokens stored in httpOnly cookies (not localStorage)
- Session timeout after 15 minutes of inactivity
- On timeout: clear all in-memory PHI, redirect to login
- MFA required for admin accounts, recommended for all users
- Password requirements: minimum 12 characters, complexity rules via Supabase

## Data Handling Rules

### Audio
- Audio NEVER persists to disk, localStorage, or sessionStorage
- Audio buffers exist only in memory during active recording
- On recording stop: buffers are immediately released
- On page unload: cleanup handler releases all audio resources
- WebSocket audio transmission uses WSS (TLS)

### Transcripts
- Stored encrypted in Supabase (database-level encryption)
- Displayed only to authenticated, authorized users (RLS)
- Never logged to console, error tracking, or analytics
- Search queries on transcripts go through server-side full-text search

### Clinical Notes
- Same encryption and access rules as transcripts
- Finalized notes are immutable (no edits after finalization)
- Version history for audit trail (store previous versions)

