## API Security
- All API routes validate JWT token
- Rate limiting: 100 req/min per user
- CORS: only allow our frontend origin
- Content-Security-Policy headers on all responses
- No PHI in URL parameters (use POST body or path params)
- Request IDs for tracing (no PHI in request IDs)

## Logging Rules
- NEVER log: patient names, DOB, MRN, transcript text, note content, audio data
- OK to log: user IDs, consultation IDs, action types, timestamps, error codes
- Structured JSON logging format
- Log retention: 7 years (HIPAA requirement)

## Database Security
- Row Level Security (RLS) on every table containing PHI
- Users can only access their own data (via auth.uid())
- Admin queries require separate admin role check
- Database connections use SSL
- Supabase handles encryption at rest

## Third-Party Services
- All services must have BAA (Business Associate Agreement):
  - Supabase: BAA available on Pro plan
  - Deepgram: BAA available for healthcare customers
  - Anthropic: Check current BAA availability
  - Vercel: BAA available on Enterprise plan
- Minimize data sent to third parties
- No PHI in error tracking (Sentry, etc.) — use sanitized error messages

## Audit Log Requirements
Log these events:
- User login/logout
- Patient record viewed
- Consultation started/ended
- Transcript viewed
- Note generated/edited/finalized
- Note exported or sent to EHR
- Settings changed
- User invited/removed (admin)

## Incident Response
- Implement breach notification hooks
- Data export capability (patient right of access)
- Data deletion capability (right to be forgotten)
- Regular access reviews (admin dashboard)
